 y = 2a(x-a) + a^2\\ y = 2b(x-b) + b^2 
 2a(x-a) + a^2 = 2b(x-b) + b^2 
 2ax - 2a^2 + a^2 = 2bx - 2b^2 + b^2\implies\\ 2ax - a^2 = 2bx - b^2 
 2ax - 2bx = a^2 - b^2\\ 2(a - b)x = a^2 - b^2 
 x = \frac 12 \frac{a^2 - b^2}{a - b} = \frac 12 \frac{(a-b)(a+b)}{a - b} = \frac 12 (a+b) 
